---
import { Icon } from "astro-icon/components";
---

<section class="quran-research-section mt-28 md:mt-36">
  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_1.05fr] gap-10 items-center rounded-[2rem] border border-accent/20 bg-accent/5 p-6 md:p-10 overflow-hidden">

    <div class="relative group order-2 lg:order-1">
      <div class="absolute -inset-6 rounded-[2rem] bg-accent/20 blur-3xl opacity-40 group-hover:opacity-70 transition-opacity duration-700"></div>

      <a
        href="https://kuranteyit.com"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="relative block overflow-hidden rounded-[1.5rem] border border-accent/20 shadow-2xl shadow-accent/10"
        aria-label="Visit KuranTeyit.com"
      >
        <img
          src="/kuranteyit-preview-v2.webp"
          alt="KuranTeyit.com Quran research platform screenshot"
          class="w-full h-full object-cover transition-transform duration-700 group-hover:scale-[1.03]"
        />
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-6 order-1 lg:order-2">

      <div>
        <p class="text-accent text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.35em] font-bold mb-4">
          Quran Research Platform
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-heading font-bold text-maintext leading-tight">
          KuranTeyit.com
        </h2>

        <p class="text-accent/90 mt-3 font-body">
          Quran study, verse analysis and research tools.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-4 text-subtext font-body leading-8">
        <p>
          Beyond music, Berk KÖKSAL is also the creator of KuranTeyit.com — a modern Quran research platform designed for reading, studying and analyzing Quran verses with a focused digital experience.
        </p>

        <p>
          The project brings together Quran reading, Arabic text, translations, verse-based tools, notes and analysis features for deeper reflection and research.
        </p>

        <p>
          KuranTeyit represents the research and software side of the same vision behind Neo-Sacred Zikr: remembering GOD, reflecting on the Quran and making sacred knowledge more accessible.
        </p>

        <p>
          KuranTeyit is an independent software project fully conceived, designed and developed from the ground up by Berk KÖKSAL, combining modern web technologies with Quran-centered research tools.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 pt-2">
        <a
          href="https://kuranteyit.com"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 rounded-full border border-accent/30 bg-accent/10 px-7 py-3 text-maintext hover:bg-accent/20 hover:scale-105 transition-all"
        >
          <Icon name="mdi:book-open-page-variant" class="w-5 h-5" />
          Visit KuranTeyit
        </a>

        <a
          href="https://kuranteyit.com"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 rounded-full border border-[#D4AF37]/30 bg-[#D4AF37]/10 px-7 py-3 text-maintext hover:bg-[#D4AF37]/20 hover:scale-105 transition-all"
        >
          <Icon name="mdi:open-in-new" class="w-5 h-5" />
          Open Platform
        </a>
      </div>

    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .quran-research-section {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(28px);
    animation: quranResearchReveal 0.9s cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1) forwards;
    animation-delay: 0.15s;
  }

  @keyframes quranResearchReveal {
    to {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: translateY(0);
    }
  }
</style>